revision.text:
The '''Blake Basin''', also called the '''Blake–Bahama Basin''', is a deep area of the [[Atlantic Ocean]] which runs along the [[east]] coast of the [[United States]]. It starts at the northern part of the [[Bahamas]] and continues up toward [[New York (state)|New York]].  Depth exceeds 5400 meters between the [[Blake Plateau]] and [[Blake Escarpment]] to the South and West, and the [[Blake Bahama Outer Ridge]].

