{{Infobox waterfall | name = Joranda Falls | photo = Joranda Water Fall Simlipal Biosphere Reserve.jpg | native_name = ଯୋରନ୍ଦା ପ୍ରପାତ | location = [[Mayurbhanj district]], [[Odisha]], [[India]] | coords = {{coord|21|56|14|N|86|24|15|E|display=title}} | elevation = | type = Plunge | height = {{convert|150|m}} | height_longest = | average_width = | number_drops = 1 | average_flow = | watercourse = }} The '''Joranda Falls''' (ଯୋରନ୍ଦା ପ୍ରପାତ୍) is located in the core area of [[Simlipal National Park]] in [[Mayurbhanj district]] in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Odisha]]. The [[Barehipani Falls]] is located close to the Joranda Falls.<ref>{{cite web |url =http://www.newodisha.in/joranda-waterfall-odisha/ |title = Joranda Falls | first= |last= |work= | publisher =Maps of India | accessdate = 2010-06-24 }}</ref> It is the 19th [[List of waterfalls in India by height|highest waterfall in India]].<ref name=database>{{cite web| last =| first =| title =Showing all Waterfalls in India| url =http://www.world-waterfalls.com/database.php?s=T&t=G&category=country&search=India&orderby=height%20DESC| publisher =World Waterfalls Database| accessdate =2010-06-24| deadurl =yes| archiveurl =https://www.webcitation.org/6AC0BJT4W?url=http://www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com/country/India/| archivedate =2012-08-25| df =}}</ref>
==The falls== The Joranda Falls has a total height of {{convert|150|m}}. The water plunges over a lofty cliff in a single drop, spreading out slightly as it falls.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.world-waterfalls.com/waterfall.php?num=858 |title = Barehipani Falls | first= |last= |work= | publisher = World Waterfall Database| accessdate = 2010-06-24 }}</ref>
