{{Politics of Montserrat}}
The '''Speaker''' is the presiding officer of the [[Legislative Assembly of Montserrat|Legislative Assembly]] of [[Montserrat]]. The Speaker is elected by MPs, and does not have to be an Assembly member.<ref name=IH>Ian Hendry & Susan Dickson (2011) ''British Overseas Territories Law'', Bloomsbury Publishing, p237</ref> There is also a Deputy Speaker, who is elected by MPs from amongst their own numbers, although they cannot also be a member of the cabinet.<ref name=IH/>
